name: UR GDG (Google Developer Group)
description: UR GDG is a community of developers interested in Google technologies. We host events, workshops, and talks to enhance your skills.

name: UR CSSS (Computer Science Students Society)
description: The Computer Science Students Society aims to bring together students passionate about technology and computer science. We organize hackathons, workshops, and guest lectures.

name: UR CyberSec (Cybersecurity Club)
description: UR CyberSec focuses on cybersecurity awareness and skill-building. Join us for workshops, capture the flag events, and guest speakers.

name: MASS (Math and Statistics Student Society)
description: MASS promotes interest in mathematics and statistics through events, tutoring sessions, and collaboration with faculty.

name: SSS (Science Student Society)
description: SSS is dedicated to fostering interest in science among students. We host talks, experiments, and community outreach programs.

name: BUGS (Bio Undergrads Society)
description: BUGS provides a platform for biology students to collaborate, share research, and engage in community service projects.
